				       This keeps coming up again and again so I feel I need to post on it. The Manifesto has always said no twinks or alts in Echelon and that's not gonna change. I'm not saying u can't have a twink or alternate, I'm saying that Echelon is not gonna support it. If you have an alternate, PLEASE do not shoot me a tell and ask me to invite it into the guild. I WILL NOT. There are alotta guilds already way ahead of us and we dont have time for this foolishness.<br>Again, i will explain in detail why im totally against this so u can try to understand before calling me a jerk or tyrrant. Here's an example :<br>Most of the new recruits into Echelon get FREE armour when they join if i can make better than what they got. This takes up ALOT of my time but i dont mind. I cant have my ppl runnin around ill-equipped. Do u know how many times i get tells sayin, 'hey this is so and so in your guild, im his alternate, and can you make me armour too?'<br>Is this fair? Do we have time for this when most ppl are strugglin to enhance their main character? Just the chat alone from alternates is too much a distraction. I have my hands full already just tryin to respond to all the direct tells and guild chat tells i receive, so that ppl dont think i'm ignorin em or don't care about them. Not to mention the tells i hafta do regarding buying and selling things. I DO NOT have time to speak to your alternate. The guild comes first.<br>Let's say a player has a bard and a ranger. He needs Grimfeather's rune for his ivy armour. He asks the guild for help getting it, the guild shows up, kills GF and the ranger gets his rune. Fine. Now, is it fair for this same player to log on his bard the next day and ask for help with a lambent quest? I dont think so. Its not fair to ask that the rest of us to help you with, or wait on you to develop, TWO characters. One level 50 is worth more, and way more powerful than TWO level 25s.<br>We need to know WHO we are as well. If we plan a raid, we of course count on Trevis, Kataria, and Dadiniq to be there. What if Dad decides he feels like playin his warrior alternate that day? We're screwed. We got no cleric. And this wood not be fair after all the time we've spent trying to develop and help our cleric, we woodnt have him when we need him. We are simply not big enuff to allow this. We dont have the time.<br>Lastly, i got issues with ppl that can't make up their mind to play one character, i'll admit that. This isnt guild policy or nothin, but im lettin u know up front i just plain dont like it. People that dont have the tenacity to stick to one character annoy me and i'd rather not play with them. These are the same ppl that never complete their quests cuz they get bored on camps. They lack the focus to see things thru to the end, and i dont wanna be bothered with ppl like that. I'm sorry.<br>I thought my loot policy wooda been more controversial than this, but this seems to be the item in the Manifesto most ppl got issue with. I'm not backing down on this or changin my mind unless the guild vetos me with a two-thirds vote.<br>If you have a twink or alternate, that's fine. I just prefer that we dont learn about it or be asked to support it in ANY way. I just dont see where that's fair.<br><br>Trevis
				     </div>
				   </td>
